If you need a little motivation to start your fitness journey NOW right before the new year, watch this… 

When the pandemic hit in 2020, that allowed ya girl to actually take time and focus on me! I discovered @effectfitness online and was so diligent while cooped up in the house. As yall know, my @themuaalexjourneytohealth page was jumping. I had a whole new outlook on life, my purpose, and my appearance. Thennnn outside opened back up so the end of 2020, 2021 and the beginning of 2022 I got a little lax and lost focus on my consistency. I didn’t fall all the way back because I was still the priority, but I was not as consistent. Starting in June I physically started going into the gym and was so nervous I couldn’t keep up because doing it and home and being there are two totally different things… but I still wasn’t consistent.

October 26, 2022 made me realize that I had 300 days til I turn 40 and something clicked. @deckedoutbeauty hit me up randomly wanting to change so we started our journey together. So here I am 9 WEEKS into this new journey of consistency and intention and it feels sooooooo good. I’ve vowed at least 3 days a week of activity and have been faithfully going to @effectfitness to get blessed every week. Going into this new year I am more focused than ever before, and as some of you noticed, the glow is quite bright… Look at how I dress now verses then!!! Night and day. 

Let this be the push you needed to create a HEALTHIER lifestyle. It ain’t about the weight or the inches, but about your overall health and your inside parts. When you feel good, you look good. Meet me at @effectfitness today at 12 and let’s get paid!!! And follow my @themuaalexjourneytohealth let’s get ahead of the new years rush lol.

So as some of y’all know if you’ve been following my latest fitness journey, I been on my grind for the last 11 weeks. That means consistently working out between 3-5 days at @effectfitness (in person), that means being more conscious of what I put in my body, tons of water a day, minimal if not NO DRINKING during the week, incorporating daily smoothies and protein shakes, that means mentally showing up for myself first and eliminating things/people who no longer serve a positive purpose in my life. 

October 23rd I realized I had 300 days until my 40th Bday and that was all the motivation I needed to get back on yet another journey. But that’s life right? We constantly on some journey or restarting some shit, and that’s ok, as long as you never give up. I dun had so many Day 1s and that’s Gahd damn fine! Don’t let nobody shame you for that… 

If you want to follow along and join me as I share my fitness journey, my healthy self care journey, how I pour into myself and how I hold myself accountable as well as just showing how I live my life to the fullest, follow me and my health page @themuaalexjourneytohealth. 

Major shouts out to @effectfitness @datgreenguy @theballeffect @callmej5 @_1lito @justin17grier @lolastaxx and all the trainers because going in person is waaaayyyyy different than virtual in the most awesome ways ever. Also big shouts out to my accountability partner and workout buddy, @deckedoutbeauty. We been riding for 11 weeks straight and have not looked back. Proud of us Derrica. Super thankful for my supportive husband @kingrio82 who motivates me just by his own journey and by positively pushing me and encouraging me by making note of my physical changes and non scale victories. 

And one time for the fact that I ain’t got “Booty/Tittay Do” no more… Where my stomach use to stick out at far as my booty and tittays do… 😭😭😭😭🤷🏾‍♀️🤷🏾‍♀️🤷🏾‍♀️🤷🏾‍♀️. My Big Bertha is slowly turning into a Medium Big Bethany… and that wagon is gettin heavy and lifted too 🍑😝

Ok so boom… Last night I was honored amongst a bunch of amazing Beauty Influencers in Atlanta at the @narsboutiqueatl. Big thanks to @miasiasymone for giving this old gal her flowers while I’m still here. I’ve been an Atlanta Makeup Artist (some would say I was an influencer before the word influencer was a thing) for almost 15 years. I started out as an Industrial Engineer freshly married and new to Atlanta and makeup way back in 2008, before Instagram and social media. It was an awesome time to be a creative because all you had were your talents and reputation. To be able to still love what I do and still be relevant 15 years later is truly an honor and a blessing. I’ve assisted many MUAs cultivate their careers, I’ve helped many beautiful women fall in love with enhancing their beauty through makeup, and most importantly, I’ve sustained a happy and healthy career doing something that I LOVE. And God told me I’m just getting started…

To all those featured in this reel and who were honored last night, CONGRATULATIONS!!! You deserve every accolade and accomplishment. I’m so proud of each and every one of you and it was a pleasure meeting some of my IG glam fam for the first time last night. Super special thanks to my rock… My reason, my best friend, my husband @kingrio82 who has held me down all these years as an aspiring makeup artist so that I could be the MUA you all know and love today. Thank you baby for being my date, taking pics, videos, carrying my gifts, for getting me cocktails, and helping me put my flip flops on at the end of the night. I love you so much and am so blessed to have you be the reason I get to pursue my dreams. 

Thank you @narsboutiqueatl @narsissist for acknowledging us artists in our Atlanta community, the event was beautiful. And thanks to all the sponsors and folks who made it happen. Job well done. 

#themmuaalex #narsboutiquebuckhead #narsboutique #mua #atlmua #atlantamua

Deep transparent l/relatable post coming in… 3… 2… 1…

This past Saturday I was honored amongst 19 other Beauty Influencers by the beautiful @miasiasymone and the wonderful team at @narsboutiqueatl. Beauty Influencer, some would say… but a Makeup Artist, that’s me fasho!!! To be at a store being honored when just over 11 years ago I worked in a similar store setting at @maccosmetics for 3 long years, it was a compete full circle moment. 

As an MUA, often times we are looked at as the “hired help”, our rates attempt to get negotiated to fit a budget, we make such a grueling and thankless job look glamorous and pretty, we are brushed off and are often times overlooked for various reasons (most reasons behind our control or unbeknownst to us.) It’s all apart of the career they say. That’s so unfortunate but so true and in my 15 years of experience, I’ve seen and experienced it all. 

During the slower days in our industry where God allows time for reflection, creative inspiration, and self care, I’ve truly tapped into the importance of valuing my clients but also valuing myself. With a clear mind, I almost decided to cancel my 40th Birthday trip so that I could be more responsible with my money and plan for safety. But PHUCK that, I’m going on my trip and I am celebrating my damn self. In a career where we are responsible for the well being and appearance of our clients as well as going above and beyond to make sure our clients are well taken care of in all aspects, I have to do that and more for myself. I trust and believe in God and always have with everything, so I know things will be great.

I say all this to say, Makeup Artists TAKE CARE OF YOURSELVES and receive these flowers that my dear Leo sister @im.angelabassett has given us. We deserve them. We’ve earned them. And we too need to be celebrated!!! Thank you to all of my loyal and new clients because without you, I would not be the artist I am today. Money, fame, and opportunities come and go, but to have a village that holds each other down is priceless… My clients ride for me and I ride for them 🤞🏾. 

And Europe, we finna paint the entire Greece and Italy red come August baby!!!!!!

It’s official… My hair is back and more luxurious than ever!!! After the Covid I had in July 2020 (the only time I’ve ever had it and I had that original Coronavirus 😷) that left me suffering from Telogen Effluvium (look it up) and some heat damage in later years, my hair is back and soooo healthy. 

I’ve shared on my stories how I got my hair back healthy and all the tools, stylists, styles, and products I used. Everything is listed in my highlights (I have two dedicated to my hair loss.) I will go in more depth with my Close Friends on the specifics of how to grew your hair out after suffering from the “alopecia” I experienced since Telogen Effluvium is technically a form of alopecia. You can join my Close Friends, just dm me so I can tell you how. 

Happy Saturday folks and major shouts out to @eleciamitchell for this beautiful style and getting my hair back healthy. Between her and @toninatural, those ladies are heaven sent!!!

15 Years Married!!! Wow. 🥲

Most of you all have been supporting us for a long time and you know our story. This song symbolized a perfect 2 min representation of our love affair. We met in 2002 in college at the ripe ages of 18 and 19 and became friends. We began officially dating in 2004 after being friends, neighbors, role dawgs, you name it… Let Mario tell it, he had eyes for me the first day he saw me when he visited University of Missouri Rolla on his recruiting trip and saw me in the gym (wit a boyfriend lol.) I graduated college in Dec 2005 and we survived a long distance relationship all the way through to when Mario graduated college in May 2006. We’ve been inseparable ever since, never broke up, never dated nor pursued anyone else except each other. Mario moved to Indiana after college since I had a job there already and he proposed February 2007 with my mom as a witness. We got married June 14, 2008 in Ocho Rios, Jamaica, shortly after, moved to Atlanta in October 2008 and the rest is what you all see today… That’s 21 YEARS!!!

This man has been my Number 1 person for so long and I still get butterflies if I pull into our garage and see his car. I get excited to see my husband. I get squirmy (in a good way) every time his hands touch my body. And I laugh at every joke this man tells. I never knew I could love a person unconditionally until God blessed me with the opportunity to love this man. Now I can’t stop loving him… We will be together FOREVER! We have withstood so much and through it all, I choose him 100%. He’s the first person I wanna share something with, he’s the first person I see in the morning and the last person I see at night. If I could, I would spend every waking minute with him (until he pisses me off.) Things never came easy to us as we faced many challenges, but he is truly my person. 

Folks, true love is out there. Even amongst all the craziness that the world will force feed you. We’ve always decided to put God first in our lives and if our relationship is a braid, God has been that third strand. I love my husband and truly can’t wait to spend the rest of our lives together. 

Happy 15 Year Wedding Anniversay @kingrio82…

Thank you all for the Anniversary well wishes. We love you all and are so happy to be a healthy and happy example of what true love looks like. We definitely are far from perfection but the love and commitment we have to each other and our marriage is unmatched. Thank you God because without him, there would be no us. 

Happy Anniversary baby @kingrio82

I really felt seen with this post so I figured I would share. I am always explaining this to @kingrio82 and how as a creative who has turned their creativity into a successful business that provides financially for my family, a break is needed when a break is needed! Since 2020 and since not working full time with Missy, that pandemic break gave me what I never knew I needed, which was a pause and to focus on my mental, physical, spiritual health and genuine happiness. You’ve obviously seen me post less and live more, and this is why. Ever since I started my career as an MUA back in 2009, I’ve always been on the grind, hustling, getting it out the mud, etc… I’ve always been responsible not only for me and my home, but for my granny, my family, my friends, my artist community, and so much more. But guess what was lacking… my own self care…

So as I quickly approach 40 on August 19th and over these past few years, you all have witnessed a glow up like no other. Not just physical but EVERYTHING. My business has been slower than usual but the way I trust God with everything is unmatched, even tho it can be scary having blind faith. God already explained to me that a slower season was necessary for me to focus on what is really important. 

I say all that to say, if a break is what you’ve been feeling deep in your soul to save yourself, TAKE YOUR BREAK and focus on you and your health in all aspects. And don’t rush it, no matter if the pace doesn’t work for other. 🫶🏾

What a difference 365 days make… 20+ lbs lost according to the scale but I’ve been losing fat and gaining muscle so it reflects an even more toned and sculpted look. One year of dedication and consistency. Hard work, no short cuts, no gimmicks, no fads…

Nov 12, 2022 vs Nov 11, 2023… 🙏🏾

If you haven’t followed my @themuaalexjourneytohealth, come join the movement. 💪🏾

So this weekend’s post had me thinking… if I showed such amazing progress in one year, I need to get some flowers for the progress I’ve shown throughout this entire journey!!!

Before the pandemic, I was my most unhealthy self… I wasn’t interested in working out, eating right, and I may have been just living a shell of the life that God wanted for me. Maybe it was some sort of depression 🤷🏾‍♀️. I was on auto pilot mode and was not putting myself first. I didn’t do anything for self care, I worked an unhealthy amount of time traveling everywhere and tolerating mistreatment. I was also  grieving my granny who had passed May 18, 2019 after years of me being her sole caregiver once I moved her to Atlanta in Feb 2015. 

When 2020 came and the world shut down, I saw that as the opportunity I needed to get my shit together and start living a healthier life. I worked out from home with @effectfitness daily while stuck in the house and I started to develop some more healthier habits. I saw glimpses of the idea that God wanted me to be great and to eliminate everything toxic. Then outside opened up and I began to fall into my old ways again and was not as dedicated as before. Still maintained my weight for the most part, but was not progressing. October 24th, 2022 (300 days before my 40th birthday), I made a pact with @deckedoutbeauty to refocus on my consistent workout routine and to develop an overall healthier lifestyle. I even incorporated @chefangelalife healthy meal prep meals weekly. I still eat out and have cocktails but have did so in moderation and on weekend for the most part. So I can’t give all the praise to this last year of dedication without recognizing publicly the glow up I’ve experienced since the beginning of 2020. By the scale it’s only 40 lbs, but as you all have witnessed, it’s been wayyyyyy more progress than just the weight. 

Big thanks to @kingrio82 and @mr.fitkonnekt for being my inspiration before all this started and always. They were always down to workout with me as I tried to figure shit out. Thank you all for the support and for going on this journey with me. @themuaalexjourneytohealth. This next year will be even better. 💪🏾❤️🙏🏾

Happy Thanksgiving yall!!!
